 is substituted for the words “officer of the United States”. The words “until a successor is appointed” are omitted as surplusage.","children":[],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"Subsection (b) is substituted for 5:626–1(c) and states the effect of ","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t10/s8544/b"},"text":"section 8544(b) of this title","children":[],"tail":"."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idab5a79bd-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idab5a79be-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3347"},"text":"Section 3347 of title 5","children":[],"tail":", referred to in text, was repealed and a new section 3347 was enacted by "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/pl/105/277/dC/tI/s151/b"},"text":"Pub. L. 105–277, div. C, title I, § 151(b)","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"date","attrib":{"date":"1998-10-21"},"text":"Oct. 21, 1998","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/112/2681-611"},"text":"112 Stat. 2681–611","children":[],"tail":", and, as so enacted, no longer contains provisions authorizing the President to direct temporary successors to duties. See "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/usc/t5/s3345"},"text":"section 3345 of Title 5","children":[],"tail":", Government Organization and Employees."}],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"amendments","id":"idab5a79bf-3a6f-11f1-a58a-d8db54b14ab5"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"Amendments","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p",